This paper is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category as it deals with the storage and processing of large volumes of time series data. It also involves defining data access and privacy policies, which are key aspects of database management. 

The paper also falls under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it proposes a cryptographic solution for protecting the confidentiality of the data while enabling authorized access. 

The cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category is also relevant as the paper discusses the design of a system for processing large volumes of data in real-time. 

The cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category is relevant as the paper proposes a system for managing and processing time series data. 

Finally, the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category is relevant as the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed system for processing large volumes of data.
